-- Arsenal Eyes Move for Schalke Defender, Express Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-09-17T10:51:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-17/arsenal-eyes-move-for-schalke-defender-express-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of
soccer stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet
links.  Arsenal Target  Arsenal could meet Schalke’s 11 million-pound ($17.5
million) asking price for Kyriakos Papadopoulous in the January
transfer window, the  Daily Express  reported.  The 21-year-old Greek defender was linked with a move to
Liverpool during the offseason, the Express said.  Lewandowski Talks  Manchester United and Chelsea could move for  Robert
Lewandowski  after the Borussia Dortmund striker’s agent said he
has held talks with Napoli, the  Daily Express  reported.  Lewandowski was thought to have all but confirmed a move to
 Bayern Munich , the Express added.  Diarra Comeback  Mahamadou Diarra could earn a new Fulham contract after
making his comeback from a nine-month injury layoff, the  Daily
Mirror  reported.  Diarra, 32, may get the last berth in coach  Martin Jol ’s
25-man squad, the Mirror said.  Bale House  Real Madrid’s Gareth Bale may buy Mesut Ozil’s 1 million-pound house in the Spanish capital, the  Daily Mirror  reported.
Bale’s move to Real led to Ozil joining Arsenal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
